Also, this is, in fact, about security.  If someone is churning out plat, experience, or other hard earned game resources in a fast and easy fashion and then selling thme to Yantis or simply using it to cheat at a game and cheapen everyone else's enjoyment of it, it is a security problem.  If this were baseball, and people were betting on who would win and lose, using corked bats, using performance enhancing drugs, or otherwise cheating, there would be no question that it was a security issue.  They integrity of the game is being stolen by those cheaters.
