<br />

<br />
Why would common knowledge about the problem be asking for a sloppy patch?  If more people know about it, then more people are thinking about possible solutions for it.  I'm not sure if you are familiar with open source software such as Linux, but a huge part of why it is so successful is that all of it's errors are on display for the world to see and possibly fix.  To me a sloppy patch would be the cheesy one done by some lone wolf at SOE that fixes the problem, but introduces three others.
